	STEPS OF A WISP RELEASE
	=======================
	- pre-cutover
	- CUTOVER
	- Build source kit
	- port WISP
	- build ship kit
	- install WISP
	- send to beta test sites

	PRE-CUTOVER
	===========
	- do a test build
	- reconstruct umf files

	CUTOVER
	=======
	- warn all users
	- ensure all files are logged into SCS
	- change version numbers
	- lock SCS
	- backup SCS
	- move QAHOLD to MASTER			SCS RELEASE
	- rename change.log files		@UPDLOGS.COM
	- write release notes

	BUILD SOURCE KIT
	================
	- build source kit on hammer		$ bldsrckit.sh
	- ensure version numbers correct
	- ensure make.include is generic

	PORT WISP
	=========
	- follow steps in 			portunix.lis/portvms.lis
	- build a QA ship kit			bldshipkit.sh
	- install a QA WISP			installqa.sh
	- QA test WISP				qawisp.lis

	BUILD SHIP KIT
	==============

	Follow instructions in portunix.lis/portvms.lis under
		CREATE THE REAL WISP SHIP KIT

	INSTALL WISP
	============

	Install the real ship kit following the WISP manual.

	SEND OUT BETA TEST KITS
	=======================

	Send out BETA TEST kits to BETA sites.

